and the valet guy
says, no I actually

00:09:30.110 --> 00:09:31.802
didn't give you
the keys because I

00:09:31.802 --> 00:09:33.760
didn't think the black
guy could drive the car,

00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:35.490
I gave you keys because
there's a John Mayer CD

00:09:35.490 --> 00:09:36.440
playing in the car.

00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:38.520
And Mitch goes, you're
absolutely right,

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:42.180
that was my CD and this is
his car but you're right.

00:09:42.180 --> 00:09:44.748
He, either way, whether
it was because he thought

00:09:44.748 --> 00:09:46.956
he had some preconceived
notion about the type of car

00:09:46.956 --> 00:09:49.900
that a black dude would
drive or the type of music

00:09:49.900 --> 00:09:51.680
that a black guy
might listen to,

00:09:51.680 --> 00:09:54.370
there is a little bit of
an unconscious bias there,

00:09:54.370 --> 00:09:55.970
and it affects us
in everything we do.

00:09:55.970 --> 00:09:58.925
Race is just a part of us,
just a part of us as humans

00:09:58.925 --> 00:10:01.050
and the way we relate and
interact with each other.

00:10:01.050 --> 00:10:04.290
So this is a good opportunity
to bring some levity to it.

00:10:04.290 --> 00:10:07.555
Obviously, there have been
some really, really heavy

00:10:07.555 --> 00:10:09.700
and serious
situations around race

00:10:09.700 --> 00:10:13.330
that have happened very
recently in our country

00:10:13.330 --> 00:10:14.500
and around the world.

00:10:14.500 --> 00:10:16.929
But I think that if
you can talk about it

00:10:16.929 --> 00:10:18.970
and bring some levity to
it-- the important thing

00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:20.990
is that the conversation
is happening.

00:10:20.990 --> 00:10:22.697
So when you tell
me that Google's

00:10:22.697 --> 00:10:24.780
having those conversations
about unconscious bias,

00:10:24.780 --> 00:10:27.692
I applaud that tremendously
because the first key is

00:10:27.692 --> 00:10:28.400
talking about it.

00:10:28.400 --> 00:10:29.690
If we're not talking about
it, if it's something

00:10:29.690 --> 00:10:31.340
we're pretending like
it doesn't exist,

00:10:31.340 --> 00:10:32.520
and we're sweeping
it under the rug,

00:10:32.520 --> 00:10:34.300
all we're doing is
fostering things that

00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:36.270
ultimately could be negative.

00:10:36.270 --> 00:10:38.080
MARJAI ROBERTS:
Definitely agree.

00:10:38.080 --> 00:10:38.580
And--

00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:38.680
WILL PACKER: That
was a good answer,

00:10:38.680 --> 00:10:40.971
we should stop right now
because that's the best I got,

00:10:40.971 --> 00:10:43.272
it's downhill from here,
guys, just going to tell you.

00:10:43.272 --> 00:10:44.730
MARJAI ROBERTS: I
definitely agree.

00:10:44.730 --> 00:10:47.677
That's one thing
