00:11:16.861 --> 00:11:18.360
written as a stand-up.

00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:21.860
And so Tone Bell, the actor
that plays Russell brilliantly,

00:11:21.860 --> 00:11:24.870
is also a stand-up, that made
him fit the role perfectly.

00:11:24.870 --> 00:11:26.480
There wasn't a
lot that we needed

00:11:26.480 --> 00:11:29.500
to do to shape a role around the
actor, which you do sometimes,

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:31.080
because in this
instance the actor

00:11:31.080 --> 00:11:32.630
really, really fit the role.

00:11:32.630 --> 00:11:36.130
He really has a lot of
the-- he's a loose guy,

00:11:36.130 --> 00:11:39.420
he's a liberal guy,
he's a fun loving guy,

00:11:39.420 --> 00:11:41.101
and he happens to be a stand-up.

00:11:41.101 --> 00:11:43.100
And him being a stand-up,
and being on the road,

00:11:43.100 --> 00:11:45.058
and having to interact
with different audiences

00:11:45.058 --> 00:11:47.480
and make them laugh, it
affects his world view.

00:11:47.480 --> 00:11:49.980
And so that's in real
life tone, and that's also

00:11:49.980 --> 00:11:51.340
the character, Russell.

00:11:51.340 --> 00:11:52.830
The thing I'll say
about this cast

00:11:52.830 --> 00:11:55.470
is that each of the
characters, they

00:11:55.470 --> 00:11:58.030
