00:11:58.030 --> 00:12:00.480
Tone Bell and Bresha Webb,
who do play a married couple,

00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:04.430
knew each other, they did have
a camaraderie prior to the show.

00:12:04.430 --> 00:12:09.175
But there is an organic,
authentic camaraderie

00:12:09.175 --> 00:12:12.350
and chemistry amongst
these four that you can

00:12:12.350 --> 00:12:14.160
see when you watch the show.

00:12:14.160 --> 00:12:16.250
And literally, it's
not just about--

00:12:16.250 --> 00:12:18.480
and I've been
fortunate to produce

00:12:18.480 --> 00:12:20.469
a lot of content--
and oftentimes,

00:12:20.469 --> 00:12:21.760
when you yell "Cut," that's it.

00:12:21.760 --> 00:12:23.344
These actors-- I
don't care if they're

00:12:23.344 --> 00:12:25.801
playing husband and wife, if
they're in an intimate bedroom

00:12:25.801 --> 00:12:26.400
scene-- "Cut."

00:12:26.400 --> 00:12:27.566
Get away from me, all right?

00:12:27.566 --> 00:12:28.864
Where is my coffee? my latte?

00:12:28.864 --> 00:12:31.030
I don't want to talk to you
until it's time to roll.

00:12:31.030 --> 00:12:35.130
These actors actually,
genuinely are a family.

00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:37.399
They're tight-knit, and they
really, really genuinely

00:12:37.399 --> 00:12:39.190
get along, and they
have a great chemistry,

00:12:39.190 --> 00:12:40.980
and they hang
outside of the set.

00:12:40.980 --> 00:12:44.500
And I bring that up
because these days

00:12:44.500 --> 00:12:47.840
authentic content is really what
is resonating with audiences.

00:12:47.840 --> 00:12:51.004
Things that feel real-- whether
it's a world, or a character,

00:12:51.004 --> 00:12:52.670
or a perspective that
you can relate to,

00:12:52.670 --> 00:12:55.302
directly or not-- if it feels
like it's really authentic,

00:12:55.302 --> 00:12:57.760
if it feels like it's something
that's very natural and not

00:12:57.760 --> 00:13:01.490
manufactured by some Hollywood
writer, producer, or director,

00:13:01.490 --> 00:13:03.560
audiences resonate towards that.

00:13:03.560 --> 00:13:05.540
They're attracted to
that kind of content.

00:13:05.540 --> 00:13:06.956
And so it's really
good that we've

00:13:06.956 --> 00:13:10.180
got a foursome that is
actually oragnically--

00:13:10.180 --> 00:13:11.300
has great chemistry.

00:13:11.300 --> 00:13:12.425
MARJAI ROBERTS: Definitely.

