MARJAI ROBERTS: Definitiely.

00:19:29.740 --> 00:19:35.250
So movies, TV, what are
some of the similarities

00:19:35.250 --> 00:19:38.076
and differences for you and
producing on both sides?

00:19:38.076 --> 00:19:39.950
WILL PACKER: It's all
about creating content.

00:19:39.950 --> 00:19:42.860
The process is different,
very different actually,

00:19:42.860 --> 00:19:45.760
in terms of creating in
the different mediums,

00:19:45.760 --> 00:19:48.780
but at the end of the day,
it's about character stories,

00:19:48.780 --> 00:19:51.129
richness, doing it
well in a quality way,

00:19:51.129 --> 00:19:52.420
and finding an audience for it.

00:19:52.420 --> 00:19:53.669
That's really what it's about.

00:19:53.669 --> 00:19:56.330
So whether it's the big
screen, for the small screen,

00:19:56.330 --> 00:20:00.280
for the digital medium,
it doesn't really matter.

00:20:00.280 --> 00:20:03.272
For me, it's about what are the
stories we're trying to tell,

00:20:03.272 --> 00:20:05.230
what are the characters
we're trying to create,

00:20:05.230 --> 00:20:08.060
and who wants to see those
characters, who will relate,

00:20:08.060 --> 00:20:10.280
or who will be attracted
to those characters

00:20:10.280 --> 00:20:10.950
in those stores.

00:20:10.950 --> 00:20:12.785
That's really the key for me.

00:20:12.785 --> 00:20:13.970
MARJAI ROBERTS: Definitely.

